                <head>Mail Robbery</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p>John C. Grove, the carrier of the mail from the depot in Staunton to the Post- office, was 
                        arrested on last Saturday by special agent McGuire, on the charge of having extracted from the 
                        mail a $20 bank note and a small quantity of gold.  The letter containing the money was a decoy 
                        letter, placed in the mail for the purpose of detecting the robber, as for some time back money 
                        and checks had been taken from the mail in this section of the State.  It is rumored that he has 
                        confessed the crime.</p>
                </transcript>
